name: src/app.js

unknown.tagValue: {String} lambdas The path to the lambdas directory
{Number} port The port for the HTTP service
{String} apiPath The request path for the api
{Boolean} log Show or repress console output

params.name: type
params.description: Type of log message to write

name: procResponse
description: Handles response from forked lambda runner procs

name: parseBody
description:
Parses the template from gateway and merges in the req.body as it's
intended property for the lambda

unknown.tagValue: {Object} the full event to be passed to the Lambda

return.description: the full event to be passed to the Lambda

name: runLambda
description:
Builds the `event` payload with the request body and the method of the
call (`operation`). Forks a new runner process to the requested lambda
then awaits messaging from the lambda

name: buildConfig
description:
Combines the default config with any passed to init and overrides (lastly)
if there are any environment variables set

name: init
description:
Initialize testing service, binds endpoints to apiPath, handles the action
(runLambda) on calls and starts listener

name: src/router.js
loadSchema
description: Loads the schema from specified file

params.name: file
params.description: The file path of the Gateway schema

name: walkSchema
description:
Walks schema to look for methods, when a method is found it creates a route
with the parent node key (the path), the current method, and the properties
of that method

params.name: prevKey
params.description: The key of the previous traversal for accessing parent/path

name: mapTemplateParams
description: Maps template params to route params

params.name: template
params.description: The template object to match against

name: buildRoutes
description:
Builds routes and adds to the express service by mapping template params to
the path/route then binding to runLambda method

name: src/runner.js
context
description: Creates the context object passed to lambdas
